original_title: Brooklyn: Manhattan Avenue - Ten Eyck Street
text:
204-206 Manhattan Ave., at the N.E. corner of Ten Eyck Street. Also seen is Ten Eyck Street, east from Manhattan Ave., and Ten Eyck Street, is watching the eviction of those unwilling to move. These buildings have been razed and modern apartments are here, made possible by the Federal Housing Act.

August 26, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.
